# Типографика

## Primary Font

Font Family: Inter
Style: Sans-serif, Modern, Geometric
Usage: Все заголовки, UI элементы, кнопки, навигация
Weights Available: Regular (400), Medium (500), Semibold (600), Bold (700)
Fallback: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif

## Secondary Font

Font Family: Georgia
Style: Serif, Classic, Readable
Usage: Длинные тексты, статьи, документы
Weights Available: Regular (400), Italic (400), Bold (700)
Fallback: Times New Roman, serif

## Monospace Font

Font Family: Fira Code
Style: Monospace, Technical
Usage: Код, технические данные, таблицы с цифрами
Weights Available: Regular (400), Medium (500)
Fallback: Courier New, monospace

## Size Scale

### Headings
H1 (Main Title): 48-64px, Bold (700), Inter
H2 (Section Title): 36-42px, Semibold (600), Inter
H3 (Subsection): 28-32px, Semibold (600), Inter
H4 (Card Title): 20-24px, Medium (500), Inter

### Body Text
Large Body: 18-20px, Regular (400), Georgia or Inter
Regular Body: 16-18px, Regular (400), Georgia or Inter
Small Body: 14-16px, Regular (400), Inter
Caption: 12-14px, Regular (400), Inter

### UI Elements
Button Text: 14-16px, Medium (500), Inter
Navigation: 14-16px, Medium (500), Inter
Labels: 12-14px, Medium (500), Inter
Tooltip: 12px, Regular (400), Inter

## Line Height (Leading)

Headings: 1.2 (tight for impact)
Body Text: 1.6 (comfortable for reading)
Captions: 1.4
UI Elements: 1.5

## Letter Spacing (Tracking)

Headings: -0.02em (slightly tighter)
Body Text: 0 (default)
All Caps: 0.05em (slightly wider for readability)
Small Text (<14px): 0.01em

## Text Alignment

Primary Content: Left-aligned
Headings: Can be centered for emphasis
Short Quotes: Can be centered
Tables/Data: Left for text, right for numbers
UI Buttons: Center

## Rules and Best Practices

1. Never use more than 2 font families in one design
2. Maintain consistent line height within text blocks
3. Use font weight (not size only) to create hierarchy
4. Ensure minimum 16px for body text (accessibility)
5. Maximum line length: 60-80 characters for readability
6. Use true italics, not slanted regular fonts
7. Avoid letter spacing <-0.05em (too tight)
8. Use semibold (600) instead of bold (700) for subtle emphasis

## Forbidden

❌ Comic Sans, Papyrus, decorative fonts
❌ Stretched or condensed text
❌ Faux bold (double-stroke)
❌ All caps for long text (max 3-4 words)
❌ Colored text on colored background without sufficient contrast
❌ Too many font sizes (stick to the scale)
❌ Underlining (except links)
❌ Center-aligned body text (hard to read)

## Specific Use Cases

### Presentations
Titles: Inter Bold, 48-64px
Subtitles: Inter Medium, 24-32px
Body: Inter Regular, 18-20px
Maximum 3 levels of hierarchy per slide

### Infographics
Titles: Inter Bold, 36-48px, uppercase if short
Data Labels: Inter Semibold, 14-18px
Descriptions: Inter Regular, 14-16px
Numbers: Inter Bold or Fira Code Medium

### Documents/Reports
Title: Inter Bold, 36-42px
Headings: Inter Semibold, 24-28px
Body: Georgia Regular, 16-18px, line-height 1.6
Captions: Inter Regular, 12-14px

### Social Media
Primary Text: Inter Bold, 32-48px (high impact)
Secondary: Inter Regular, 16-20px
Very short text preferred (3-7 words max)
